# 2048 Game

This is a simple version of the popular **2048 game** made in Java. You can play it in your browser using Replit or run it locally in IntelliJ.

---

## How to Play

- Use the **arrow keys** on your keyboard to move the tiles:
  - **Up Arrow** – move all tiles up  
  - **Down Arrow** – move all tiles down  
  - **Left Arrow** – move all tiles left  
  - **Right Arrow** – move all tiles right  
- When two tiles with the same number touch, they **merge into one tile** with the sum of their values.  
- Each move will add a new tile with the number **2 or 4** in a random empty spot.  
- Your goal is to **create a tile with the number 2048**!  

---

## Rules

1. Only tiles with the **same number** can merge.  
2. Tiles slide in the direction of the arrow key **until they hit the edge or another tile**.  
3. If there are **no moves left**, the game ends.  
4. Keep merging tiles to reach **2048 or higher**.  

